<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="transcription">Transcription</a> - <a href="#transcription">Transcription</a> is the process of creating an <a href="#rna">RNA</a> transcript based on information in <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>. A <a href="#promoter">promoter</a> drives <a href="#transcription">transcription</a> and decides when and how much transcript is made. The transcript or resulting <a href="#mrna">mRNA</a> is then transformed into a <a href="#protein">protein</a> in a process called <a href="#translation">translation</a>.